This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it presents a novel approach to deformable object manipulation. It also involves generating velocity commands for grippers, which is a common task in robotics. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Multi-Armed Bandit and Kalman Filtering, which are commonly used in robotics research. 

The paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves machine learning techniques. 

The Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also likely as the paper proposes a framework that estimates changes in the utility of each model and balances exploration and exploitation. 

The Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category is possible as the paper may involve visual perception of the deformable object. 

Finally, the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is possible as the paper involves controlling the grippers to manipulate the deformable object.
